  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best way make extra money?",
  "response": "Making extra money can be approached in various ways depending on your skills, interests, and the amount of time you can commit. Here are some ideas:\n\n1. **Freelancing**: Use your skills (writing, graphic design, web development, etc.) on platforms like Upwork, Fiverr, or Freelancer.\n\n2. **Online Tutoring**: Offer your expertise in subjects like math, science, languages, or even music through platforms like VIPKid or Tutor.com.\n\n3. **Gig Economy Jobs**: Consider driving for rideshare services (Uber, Lyft), delivering food (DoorDash, UberEats), or completing tasks via TaskRabbit.\n\n4. **Renting Space**: If you have extra space, consider renting it out on Airbnb or renting a room long-term.\n\n5. **Selling Items**: Declutter and sell unused items on platforms like eBay, Craigslist, or Facebook Marketplace.\n\n6. **Investing**: If you have some money saved, consider investing in stocks, ETFs, or cryptocurrencies, but be sure to do your research.\n\n7. **Affiliate Marketing**: If you have a blog or social media presence, you can earn money by promoting products and earning a commission for sales made through your referral links.\n\n8. **Creating Online Content**: Start a YouTube channel, podcast, or blog focusing on topics you enjoy, and monetize through ads, sponsorships, or merchandise.\n\n9. **Pet Sitting or Dog Walking**: Utilize websites like Rover or Wag to find clients in your area.\n\n10. **Virtual Assistant Work**: Help businesses with administrative tasks, social media management, or customer service remotely.\n\n11. **Participating in Research Studies or Surveys**: Websites like Survey Junkie or UserTesting pay for your opinions or testing products.\n\n12. **Handyman Services**: If you are skilled in repairs or maintenance, offer your services locally or through platforms like Thumbtack.\n\nChoose an option that aligns best with your skills and interests to maximize your chances of success!",
